Panchang - Class in indiancalendar
Panchang class is used for telling the Panchang and month of Indian luni-solar calendar for the Gregorian Date given Panchang includes five parts: Tithi Nakshatra Yog Karana Vaar
Panchang() - Constructor for class indiancalendar.Panchang
Initializes a newly created Panchang object that does nothing.

RiseAndSet - Class in indiancalendar
This class is used for telling the sunrise, sunset, moonrise and moonset timings for the Gregorian Date given All calculations are done for the Delhi's location 28°36'46.2"N 77°13'51.9"E
